    interviewQuestions: [{q:"What is auto-configuration in Spring Boot?",a:"Auto-configuration automatically configures Spring Boot applications based on dependencies on the classpath. It uses @ConditionalOnClass, @ConditionalOnMissingBean, and other conditions to apply configuration.",diff:"Medium"},{q:"Explain the Spring IoC container.",a:"IoC (Inversion of Control) container manages object creation, configuration, and dependency injection. ApplicationContext is the main interface. Beans are managed singleton objects. DI can be constructor, setter, or field-based.",diff:"Hard"},{q:"What is Spring Data JPA?",a:"Spring Data JPA simplifies JPA-based data access layers. It provides repository interfaces with CRUD operations out of the box. Supports custom query methods, JPQL, specifications, and auditing.",diff:"Medium"},{q:"How does Spring Security handle authentication?",a:"Spring Security uses a filter chain for authentication. AuthenticationManager delegates to AuthenticationProviders. UserDetailsService loads user data. PasswordEncoder verifies credentials. SecurityContext stores the authenticated user.",diff:"Hard"},{q:"What are Spring Boot Actuator endpoints?",a:"Actuator exposes production-ready endpoints: /health, /info, /metrics, /env, /beans, /mappings, /configprops. They provide monitoring, metrics, and operational information. Essential for production monitoring.",diff:"Easy"},{q:"Explain Spring profiles.",a:"Profiles segregate configuration into groups (dev, test, prod). Use @Profile annotation or spring.profiles.active property. Profile-specific properties override defaults. Enables different configs per environment.",diff:"Easy"}],
